  "text": "As color feature based clustering methods do not take into account the spatial information for segmentation, the resulting outputs may have disjoint region components that should have been considered as unified objects. Consequently, it is crucial to introduce spatial constraints to this feature-based clustering process. In our analysis, we use a multivariate kernel density estimator with a combination of a color-and a spatial-based kernel defined in a product form [CITATION_1] :",
